org.incava.ijdk.lang

Interface Comparing<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultComparing, Str, Version

    public interface Comparing<T>
extends java.lang.Comparable<T>
    Extensions to the Comparable interface. This normalizes the return value to -1, 0, and 1, and adds the methods lt, lte, gt, gte, which parallel the equals method. This is similar to Ruby, where defining the <=> method (the "spaceship" method) results in the equivalent generation of <, <=, etc.
